snippet: American Jordan Spieth shot a two-under-par 69 for a share of a one-stroke lead with locals Greg Chalmers and Brett Rumford after blustery conditions caused chaos in the third round of the Australian Open on Saturday....

headline.print_headline: Spieth Shares Lead After McIlroy Blows Up in Sydney
headline.main: Spieth Shares Lead After McIlroy Blows Up in Sydney

lead_paragraph: American Jordan Spieth shot a two-under-par 69 for a share of a one-stroke lead with locals Greg Chalmers and Brett Rumford after blustery conditions caused chaos in the third round of the Australian Open on Saturday.
